#Installing minikube on windows 8 and above.

#Check if visualization is supported by running
systeminfo
#OUTPUT:
If u see the following output, hyperv is installed.
Hyper-V Requirements:      A hypervisor has been detected. Features required for
Hyper-V will not be displayed.

Inatall minikube on windows (Source: https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/start/)

Minikube Prerequisites:
Docker
2 CPUs or more
2GB of free memory
20GB of free disk space
Internet connection
Container or virtual machine manager, such as: Docker, Hyperkit, Hyper-V, 
KVM, Parallels, Podman, VirtualBox, or VMware Fusion/Workstation

minikube is local Kubernetes, focusing on making it easy to learn and develop for Kubernetes.

All you need is Docker (or similarly compatible) container or a Virtual Machine environment, 
and Kubernetes is a single command away: minikube start

Download the latest release here: https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-installer.exe

Check if minikube is running on cygwin by typing:
minikube
minikube start #on windows 10 home edition only


